column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Mostly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Calm Wind
column14: EHSN does not calculate effective depth correctly when there is a slush observation; it incorrectly applies the meter below footing offset, resulting in erroneous depth of observation. Caught error on panel tag mark 45.3 when the 0.5 when depth of observation was below the total depth. Corrected depth of observation manually after error was discovered, but previous panels are incorrect when there is slush. This error results in 0.1 m added to effective depth, and then computes an incorrect depth of observation based on  the incorrect effective depth, thus overestimating flow.  Re-did measurement using trimble. Discovered flow at tag mark 13.0 m and 7.5 m, revised LB edge to 5.0 m. EHSN would not allow LB edge to be revised and would not allow panels to be inserted outside that 13.0 m LB boundary. Values on front page are from Trimble. Measurements will be good for comparison once LB is revised on EHSN measurement,  HFC Comments: Control Condition: ICEMeasurement Section Codition: ICEWeather Condition: OVECAST  Corrected M.G.H. includes Sensor Reset Correction of -0.004 and Gage Correction of 0.000 applied to Weighted M.G.H of 1.360 no purge, no reset applied to logger
